 When Wells Fargo engages in two or more consumer credit sales‚Äîother than sales pursuant to a revolving credit account‚Äîand has the same collateral secure the underlying debts, or, alternatively, Wells Fargo elects to consolidate the debts into one debt payable on a single payment schedule secured by cross-collateral security interests, then Wells Fargo must (a) apply payments to the debts according to the order of the sales made, and (b) must terminate its security interests in the collateral as the debts secured by each piece of collateral are paid. 

 1. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Asset Based Loans; 
 2. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Commercial Credit Cards;
