 4. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Consumer Other Loans/Lines;
 5. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Non-Consumer Loans/Lines;
 6. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Other Commercial/Wholesale Loans & LOC;
 7. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Structured Products;
 8. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Trade Finance;
 9. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Commercial Real Estate Loans;
 10. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Consumer Real Estate; and
 11. Other Services ‚Äì Securitization 

 Generally Applicable Supporting Citations: Colo. Rev. Stat. ¬ß 5-3-203(1); D.C. Code ¬ß 28-3805(a); Fla. Stat. ¬ß 520.351(1); Iowa Code ¬ß 537.3303(1); Idaho Code ¬ß 28-43-303(1); Ind. Code ¬ß 24-4.5-2-409(1); Kan. Stat. Ann. ¬ß 16a-3-303(1); Me. Stat. tit. 9-A, ¬ß 3-303(1); Okla. Stat. tit. 14A, ¬ß 2-409(1); W. Va. Code ¬ß 46A-2-109(1).

 State-Specific Restrictive Requirements: 

 1. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Asset Based Loans; Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Commercial Credit Cards; Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Consumer Credit Cards; Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Consumer Other Loans/Lines; Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Non-Consumer Loans/Lines; Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Other Commercial/Wholesale Loans & LOC; Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Structured Products; Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Trade Finance; Other Services ‚Äì Securitization.

 a. If Wells Fargo elects to consolidate the debts secured by cross-collateral, and the debts arose from two or more sales made on the same day, Wells Fargo must apply payments first to the payment of the smallest debt. (CO, FL) Colo. Rev. Stat. ¬ß 5-3-203(3); Fla. Stat. ¬ß 516.31(4). 

 b. For revolving, or open ended, credit accounts secured by cross-collateral, Wells Fargo must apply payments first to the payment of finance charges in the order of their entry to the account and then to the payment of debts in order the debts were incurred. (CO, ID) Colo. Rev. Stat. ¬ß 5-3-203(2); Idaho Code ¬ß 28-43-303(2). 

 c. When Wells Fargo engages in two or more consumer credit sales‚Äîother than sales pursuant to a revolving credit account‚Äîand has the same collateral secure the underlying debts, or, alternatively, Wells Fargo elects to consolidate the debts into one debt payable on a single payment schedule secured by cross-collateral security interests, then Wells Fargo must apply payments pro rata to the payment of the debts arising from the sales. (SC) S.C. Code Ann. ¬ß 37-2-409(1). 

 d. When Wells Fargo engages in two or more retail installment sale agreements or sales under revolving credit agreements, and those agreements are consolidated into one debt payable on a single schedule and also secured by cross-collateral security interests, Wells Fargo must apply payments to the debts according to the order of sales made. (MA) Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 255D, ¬ß 18(B). 

 e. For a consumer lease, Wells Fargo must not take a cross-collateral security interest in property of the lessee to secure debt arising from the lease. (IN, ME, OK) Ind. Code. ¬ß 24-4.5-2-407(2); Me. Stat. tit. 9-A, ¬ß 3-301(2); Okla. Stat. tit. 14A, ¬ß 2-407(2).

 f. In a consumer credit sale of a motor vehicle, if Wells Fargo takes a cross-collateral security interest in any other motor vehicle, as well as the motor vehicle subject of the sale, the total amount secured cannot exceed the amount of the sale price of the motor vehicle and Wells Fargo must not advance money or other things of value to be included in the transaction. (OK) Okla. Stat. tit. 14A, ¬ß 2-112.

 2. Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Commercial Real Estate Loans and Lending Product (loans, lines and leases) ‚Äì Consumer Real Estate

 a. Any mortgage lender, broker, loan originator, loan officer, or other Wells Fargo employee required to be licensed must not take an interest in any collateral securing a mortgage except for real estate or residential property. (DC) D.C. Code ¬ß 26-1114(a)(2). 

 b. For an open-end mortgage that secures future advances, Wells Fargo must identify the mortgage at the beginning thereof as an ‚Äúopen-end mortgage‚Äù and clearly state that it secures future advances. (PA) 42 PA. Cons. Stat. ¬ß 8143(f).

